## Discussion

In this study, we investigated the applicability domain of the PluriLum assay and related our findings to current knowledge on developmental toxicity of the test compounds. In addition, we have compared our findings and the performance of the assay to similar in vitro test systems designed to utilize embryonic or pluripotent stem cells and cardiomyocyte differentiation for assessment of developmental toxicity.

